Third-party code vendored in this repository:

musikr (module :musikr)
  Source:  https://github.com/OxygenCobalt/Auxio (dev branch, package
           org.oxycblt.musikr)
  License: GNU General Public License v3.0
  Notes:   Vendored verbatim/adapted from the Auxio project. Provides local
           music scanning (Storage Access Framework), tag extraction (via
           TagLib), cover art handling, playlist storage and caching. Not
           written by the Vinilo project; all credit for its design and
           implementation belongs to the Auxio authors and contributors.

TagLib (native library, musikr/src/main/cpp/taglib)
  Source:  https://github.com/taglib/taglib
  License: GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 / Mozilla Public License 1.1
           (dual-licensed; see upstream COPYING files)
  Notes:   Used by musikr via JNI for audio metadata extraction.

Planned integrations (not yet vendored, to be added in future phases):

  - NewPipeExtractor (https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipeExtractor) —
    GNU General Public License v3.0. Will be used to extract audio streams
    from YouTube search results. Vinilo does not act as a YouTube client;
    videos are never played, only their audio is used.
  - MusicBrainz (https://musicbrainz.org) — public API, used to enrich
    metadata for downloaded tracks.
  - Cover Art Archive (https://coverartarchive.org) — public API, used as a
    fallback source for album artwork.

